data.name: ReplaceSpecialBands.ToolTip
data.value: By default, for songs such as Metallica or Van Halen songs, GHWT: DE will populate the character slots with specific, per-song band members. If this is checked, the game will ignore this behavior and use characters in the preferred member slots, or it will select characters at random to fill the empty member slots.

data.name: PreferredFemaleSinger.ToolTip
data.value:
Who will be seen as the default female vocalist? This only triggers in female lead singer songs.
For Rock Star Creator characters, use "custom_character_x", where x is the index of the character seen in ALPHABETICAL ORDER in your Profiles folder. If you wish to view these characters and get their indexes, visit the Rock Star Creator Character Manager.
For character mods, use the name of the FOLDER in your mods folder. If you're unsure on the name of the folder, select the folder selector ("...") button to the right of this text box.
For built-in characters, visit the "ID_Characters.txt" file in the Resources directory of your game folder.
If this is blank or the specified character does not exist, the game will, at random, select any character.

data.name: AlwaysVOIntro.ToolTip
data.value:
Makes the pre-song interventions by James Hetfield always on by default.
Note that if this is checked, intro animation sequences like Ecstacy of Gold seen on For Whom the Bell Tolls will not be displayed before the song starts.
It is also worth noting that if you wish to see the unique animations for songs like Panama or FWTTB, they must be played in their original venues for the intro sequence to trigger; they will not be seen on unrelated venues.

data.name: PreferredStage.ToolTip
data.value:
What venue do you want the game to select by default? This will set the preferred venue in the Quickplay Options menu before starting.
Any compatible venue mods are listed at the bottom of the dropdown menu.

data.name: HUDTheme.ToolTip
data.value:
The style of the HUD (heads up display) seen on the screen during songs.
• GH: World Tour+ (Default): The same as the vanilla GHWT interface, but adds a song time meter above the score in single player and under the score in multiplayer. • Guitar Hero: World Tour: The vanilla, original HUD style in the game. • Guitar Hero: Metallica: Takes on the appearance of Guitar Hero: Metallica's HUD design with the star meter, band HUD improvements, colored multiplier numbers, and more! • Guitar Hero: Smash Hits: Same as Guitar Hero: Metallica's HUD, but with the sleek, gold look seen in Guitar Hero: Smash Hits along with a star earned sound effect! • Guitar Hero: Van Halen: Same as Guitar Hero: Metallica's HUD, but with a few minor visual tweaks, sound effect changes, and font changes.
Note that all post-GHWT themes (GHM, GHSH, GHVH) will use different sound effects and fonts to compliment their original appearances in their respective games.

data.name: TapTrailTheme.ToolTip
data.value:
The style of the line connecting tap notes in a tap section.
• GH: World Tour (Default): Tap notes are connected by a purple line. • Guitar Hero: Metallica: Tap notes are connected by a gray line. • No Tap Trail: The tap trail will not be displayed.

data.name: AudioBuffLen.ToolTip
data.value:
In bytes, the length of the audio buffer used when decoding FMOD streams. Higher is usually better, but changing this or changing your speaker output frequency can potentially cause bad audio output.
For most users, leave this on 4096. If audio begins to sound bad, turn this down to a lower value.

data.name: MuteStreams.ToolTip
data.value: When this is enabled, if a note is missed, it mutes out the current instrument track until another note is successfully hit. Unchecking this disables this behavior, and all audio tracks will be audible regardless of notes missed.

data.name: RichPresence.ToolTip
data.value:
Uses Discord's rich presence feature.
If this is enabled, when you're playing GHWT: DE, this will update your Discord status with various details about the song you're playing, the difficulty and instrument you're playing on, how much longer until the song is over, and other cool little things!

data.name: AutoLaunchEnabled.ToolTip
data.value:
Enable or disable auto launch.
When this is enabled, WTDE will automatically load into a song of your choosing! You can also set the bot usage, instruments, difficulties, venue, and more.
Warning: This may erase your save data, so make sure to back it up first!

data.name: KeyBindsParentPanel.ToolTip
data.value:
This list shows all of the keyboard inputs you can rebind.
To add an input, click "Add". To clear all inputs for that control, click "Clear".
Make sure to click "Save Key Binds" when you're finished editing your controls!

data.name: DisableSongLogging.ToolTip
data.value:
Turn ON or OFF writing to the debug log while songs are being played.
While songs are running in-game, this will disable any sort of logging to the debug log, which may improve performance slightly. However, while OFF, in the event of crashes that occur mid-song, this won't exhibit a helpful debug log.

data.name: DebugDLCSync.ToolTip
data.value:
Enable or disable song sync debugging.
While playing online, a sync is performed to ensure all players have identical copies of the same songs. If this is ON, this will write all syncing information to the debug log.
